Utterance: Hi Ellie! It’s nice to see you again. How have you been since our last session?
Hi! I’ve been doing well, thanks. I actually tried writing down my thoughts before bed, and it helped a lot!
That’s fantastic! I’m glad to hear that. How did it feel to write everything down?
It felt freeing, like I could let go of the worries for the night. I didn’t feel as anxious about the next day.
That’s a great outcome! It sounds like you found a helpful strategy. Did you notice any changes in your sleep quality?
Yes, I think I slept better overall. I still have some nights where it’s tough, but it’s improving.
That’s a positive step forward. Have you been able to incorporate any mindfulness practices as well?
I tried the breathing exercises we did together, and I actually liked it! I do it for a few minutes every day now.
That’s wonderful to hear! How has it impacted your daily life?
I feel calmer and more present. It helps me when I start to feel overwhelmed with everything.
That’s excellent progress! It sounds like you’re finding ways to manage your anxiety effectively. Have you noticed any other changes in your mood or energy levels?
I feel more energized during the day, which is nice. I’m able to be more present with my baby, too.
That’s great! Being present is so important. Have you had any moments with your baby that stood out to you recently?
Yes! We had a fun day at the park last weekend. Just watching him explore was so heartwarming.
That sounds lovely! Those moments can be really special. Have you been able to take time for yourself as well?
I did! I took a short walk by myself while my husband watched the baby. It felt nice to have that break.
That’s wonderful! Self-care is crucial, especially as a parent. How do you feel about continuing to prioritize that time for yourself?
I think I need to make it a regular thing. It really helps me recharge.
Absolutely! Setting aside time for yourself will benefit both you and your family. Is there anything specific you’d like to do for self-care this week?
I’d love to read a book I’ve been meaning to get into. I’ll make some time for that!
That sounds like a great plan! Reading can be a wonderful escape. Now, let’s talk about your goals for your child psychology courses. Have you made any progress?
Yes! I enrolled in a couple of online modules, and I’ve started my first one. It’s challenging but exciting!
That’s fantastic! How are you feeling about the coursework so far?
It’s a lot of information, but I’m enjoying it. I feel like I’m learning so much already.
That’s great to hear! Remember to take breaks and pace yourself. Have you been able to connect with any peers in the courses?
Not yet, but I’m thinking about joining a discussion forum to meet others.
That’s a wonderful idea! Connecting with others can provide support and motivation. How do you feel about reaching out to others?
I’m a bit shy about it, but I know it could be beneficial.
It’s completely normal to feel shy. Maybe you could start by commenting on a post or sharing your thoughts in the forum.
That sounds manageable. I’ll give it a try!
Great! I’m looking forward to hearing how that goes. Now, let’s circle back to your relationship with your mom. Have you had a chance to share more with her?
I did! I told her about my courses and how I’m feeling. She was really supportive and offered to help with the baby when I study.
That’s wonderful! It sounds like you’re building a strong support system. How did it feel to open up to her?
It felt good! I think it brought us closer, and I felt less alone in my journey.
That’s fantastic! Building that connection is so valuable. Is there anything else you’d like to work on today?
I’d like to talk about how to handle stress when things get overwhelming. I sometimes struggle with that.
That’s a great topic. What specific situations tend to trigger your stress?
When the baby is crying, and I have a lot to do, I feel like I can’t handle it all.
It’s understandable to feel overwhelmed in those moments. Have you thought about any techniques to help you manage that stress when it arises?
I haven’t really. I just tend to freeze up and feel panic.
One technique you could try is grounding yourself. When you start to feel overwhelmed, take a moment to focus on your breath and remind yourself of your surroundings.
That sounds helpful. I could try that when things get chaotic.
Absolutely! It can help bring you back to the present moment. Would you like to set a goal to practice that this week?
Yes, I’ll work on it. Thank you!
You’re welcome! It sounds like you’re making great strides in managing your emotions and building your future. I’m really proud of you.
Thank you! I appreciate your support.
Of course! I look forward to hearing about your progress next time. Take care of yourself this week!
I will! Bye!
Goodbye!
